Recent changes: Added neighbor counting logic. For each living cell, counts adjacent living cells and keeps those with 2 or 3 neighbors. Uses nested filter with coordinate comparison.

Current implementation:
```typescript
export type Cell = [number, number];

export function nextGeneration(livingCells: Cell[]): Cell[] {
  return livingCells.filter((cell) => {
    const neighborCount = livingCells.filter(
      (other) =>
        !(other[0] === cell[0] && other[1] === cell[1]) &&
        Math.abs(other[0] - cell[0]) <= 1 &&
        Math.abs(other[1] - cell[1]) <= 1
    ).length;
    return neighborCount === 2 || neighborCount === 3;
  });
}
```

